nodes.bodyText:
This can be simplified:

We know remainingLength >= usrLibLength else strstr() would have returned NULL.
It's safe to peek at the character at needle[usrLibLength] unconditionally (at worst it's the NUL terminator).

    if ((':' == needle[usrLibLength]) || ('\0' == needle[usrLibLength])) {
        /* Found a match */
        appendToLibPath = FALSE;
        break;
    }

Nesting it within the inverse of the if statement above we can remove the goto and the label:
    if ((0 == offsetFromStart) || (':' == needle[-1])) {
        if ((':' == needle[usrLibLength]) || ('\0' == needle[usrLibLength])) {
            /* Found a match */
            appendToLibPath = FALSE;
            break;
        }
    }

